I have been making this recipe for many years and thought it was time to give my praise to it online. It is a GREAT coating for chicken! I have made it in the oven, as the recipe envisions, but now I usually double the vinaigrette and cover smaller whole chickens (4 lb chickens - 2 or 3 of them) with the vinaigrette and throw them on the grill. Since there is no sugar in the vinaigrette, the coating doesn't burn and the chickens come out moist and the flavor is fabulous.

