Rating: 3
When preparing this dish I made two mistakes which may have contributed to making it even more delicious: I put the chicken breast side down on a rack in a roasting pan, and I broiled it for the first 30 to 45 minutes. To make up for those mistakes, I basted the back with what was left of the vinaigrette, and I turned the chicken over and broiled the breast side for the last 5-10 minutes. As a result, the skin was really nicely cooked and the breasts were incredibly moist. I also strained the pan juices, removed most of the fat, and served it on the side. It was very, very good!

